[敬邀蒞臨]2012/12/15《智慧財產權、社會經濟生活與原住民族研究國際研討會》
2012 年 12 月 07 日 · by admin · in 2012 年, 學會成員活動, 最新消息, 研究活動, 研討會 



2012/12/15
“Intellectual Property, Socio-Economic Life and Indigenous Peoples- An International Seminar Reflecting the Current Development”
《智慧財產權、社會經濟生活與原住民族研究國際研討會》


舉辦日期：2012年12月15日(週六) 10:00~16:30


舉辦地點：公務人力發展中心福華國際文教會館101室 (地址： 臺北市新生南路三段30號)


指導單位：行政院國家科學委員會


主辦單位：國立清華大學科技法律研究所


協辦單位：台灣法學會國際法研究委員會、台灣加拿大研究學會


報名網址：http://ppt.cc/VUpW 

本研討會會議全程語言為英文
本研討會座位有限，將於2012/12/13(週四)公告並寄送報名錄取名單。敬請報名者詳實填寫報名資訊，以作為主辦單位錄取之參考資料。





2012/12/15 研討會議程：







2012年12月15日 (週六)



Time
Agenda


09:30～10:00
Reception


10:00～10:10
Open Address：Tay-Sheng Wang (王泰升),
 Distinguished Professor, College of Law, National Taiwan University, TAIWAN (President of Taiwan Law Society)


10:10～10:50
Topic：On Policy Measures for the Socio-Economic Betterment of the Ainu People
Speaker：Prof. Teruki Tsunemoto, Director and Prof of Law, Hokkaido University Center for Ainu and Indigenous Studies, JAPAN
 Prof. Ken’ichi Ochiai, Assistant Prof of Law, Hokkaido University Center for Ainu and Indigenous Studies, JAPAN
Moderator：Tay-Sheng Wang
 (王泰升),
 Distinguished Professor, College of Law, National Taiwan University, TAIWAN


10:50～11:30
Topic：Law(s) and Traditional Ecological Knowledge : Legal Pluralism on Sediq Truku Territory
Speaker：Scott Simon, Associate Professor, Department of Sociology and Anthropology, University of Ottawa, CANADA


11:30～12:00
General Discussion：Chairman：Tay-Sheng Wang (王泰升),
 Distinguished Professor, College of Law, National Taiwan University, TAIWAN


12:00～13:30
Lunch


13:30～14:10
Topic：Formalizing Authenticity – The Implementation of the Indigenous Traditional Intellectual Creation Protection Act
Speaker：Chris Chu-Cheng Huang (黃居正), Associate Professor, Institute of Law for Science and Technology, National Tsing Hua University, TAIWAN (President of Association of Canadian Study in Taiwan)
Moderator：Cheng-feng Shih
 (施正鋒), Professor,
 Department of Indigenous Development and Social Work, National Dong Hwa University, TAIWAN


14:10~14:50
Topic：The Indigenous Industries in Taiwan and Governmental Supports: in the context of Taiwan’s Accession to the World Trade Organization
Speaker ：William Hui-Yen Hsu (徐揮彥), Associate Professor, Graduate Institute of Financial and Economic Law, National Dong Hwa University, TAIWAN


14:50～15:10
Tea Time


15:10～15:50
Topic：Indigenous Culture as a Foundation of Economy Autonomy – Taking the Millet Production Culture of the Lalauran Tribe as an Example
Speaker ：Awi Mona (Chih-Wei Tsai 蔡志偉), Associate Professor, Department of Indigenous Development and Social Work, National Dong Hwa University, TAIWAN
Moderator：Chris Chu-Cheng Huang (黃居正), Associate Professor, Institute of Law for Science and Technology, National Tsing Hua University, TAIWAN


15:50～16:30
General Discussion：Chairman：Chris Chu-Cheng Huang (黃居正), Associate Professor, Institute of Law for Science and Technology, National Tsing Hua University, TAIWAN (President of Association of Canadian Study in Taiwan)




研討會議程下載:2012_conference_agenda_final_TW_virsion


